import{A as e}from"./UIcon.c2db81b6.js";import{g as a}from"./skills.f303cb0e.js";const n=[{slug:"hsa-project",color:"green",description:`
The HSA Management project at HSA Bank is a comprehensive platform designed to help individuals and employers manage various health-related savings accounts, such as Health Savings Accounts (HSAs), Flexible Spending Accounts (FSAs), and Health Reimbursement Arrangements (HRAs). The project primarily focuses on providing users with the tools and resources to manage their healthcare expenses and savings efficiently, with a strong emphasis on user autonomy and ease of use.
<h3>Key Features of the HSA Management Project</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Self-Service Portal</b>: Users can manage their accounts, check balances, track spending, and make reimbursements for healthcare-related expenses directly through the platform. This feature reduces the need for customer support and empowers users to take control of their financial health.</li>
<li><b>Automated Tax Reporting</b>: The platform includes an automated tax reporting feature, which allows users to generate necessary tax documents related to their HSA or FSA accounts. This ensures compliance with tax regulations and simplifies the process of filing taxes for account holders.</li>
<li><b>Real-Time Notifications</b>: Users receive real-time alerts for account updates, such as when their balance changes or when a new transaction occurs. This helps users stay informed and engaged with their account activity.</li>
<li><b>Cloud Infrastructure</b>: Built on Azure (or AWS, depending on earlier versions), the platform is scalable, secure, and highly available. It leverages cloud services to handle real-time data processing for millions of users, ensuring that the system remains responsive and efficient, even during peak usage times.</li>
<li><b>API Integration</b>: The project integrates with third-party payroll and healthcare systems, allowing seamless data exchange between HSA Bank and other services. This ensures that the platform is versatile and can easily work alongside existing employer or healthcare systems.</li>
<li><b>Enhanced Security</b>: Security is a critical aspect of the platform. It implements industry-standard encryption, secure data transmission, and multi-factor authentication to protect sensitive healthcare and financial data, ensuring compliance with regulations like HIPAA and IRS guidelines.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Objectives</h3>
<ul>
<li>To provide a user-friendly platform for managing healthcare savings.</li>
<li>To streamline the process of handling healthcare-related expenses for users.</li>
<li>To ensure compliance with tax laws and healthcare regulations through automated features.</li>
<li>To offer real-time visibility and control over financial health, helping users save for current and future medical needs.</li>
</ul>
The HSA Management Project aims to make health savings management more accessible and convenient, improving the overall financial well-being of its users.`,shortDescription:"Developed and optimized web applications using ASP.NET Core and Vue.js, improving scalability and user experience for managing health savings accounts.",links:[{to:"https://www.hsabank.com/",label:"Website"}],logo:e.HSABank,name:"HSA Account Management System",period:{from:new Date(2023,1),to:new Date(2024,9)},skills:a("csharp","dotnet","vue","typescript","azure","mssql","git","agile","redis"),type:"Financial Service",screenshots:[{label:"HSA Bank Overview",src:"https://i.ibb.co/LCPw4mg/hsabank.jpg"}]},{slug:"tapcheck-project",color:"cyan",description:`
The Tapcheck Earned Wage Access (EWA) Platform allows employees to access a portion of their wages before payday. This project helps employees avoid financial stress by giving them flexible access to their earned wages whenever needed, without disrupting the employerâ€™s payroll process. It integrates seamlessly with payroll systems to track employee earnings in real time, ensuring accuracy and reliability.
<h3>Key Features of the Tapcheck Earned Wage Access Platform</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Earned Wage Access (EWA)</b>: The platform allows employees to withdraw a portion of their earned wages before payday via a mobile app, helping them manage bills, rent, and other financial obligations without waiting for their paycheck.</li>
<li><b>Payroll System Integration</b>: The platform is integrated with employer payroll systems, enabling real-time tracking of employee earnings, ensuring accurate wage availability and automating the deduction from their paycheck.</li>
<li><b>Mobile App for Easy Access</b>: Employees can access their wages and track their balances through a simple mobile app, making it user-friendly and convenient to handle wage withdrawals.</li>
<li><b>Cloud Infrastructure</b>: Hosted on AWS, the platform uses services like EC2, RDS, and S3 to ensure high availability, scalability, and secure storage of data.</li>
<li><b>Real-Time Notifications</b>: Employees receive alerts for successful withdrawals, upcoming payday, and balance updates, improving financial transparency.</li>
<li><b>Compliance and Security</b>: Tapcheck adheres to strict industry security standards, ensuring employee data and financial transactions are safe and compliant with regulations.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Objectives</h3>
<ul>
<li>Provide employees with financial flexibility through access to earned wages when needed.</li>
<li>Ensure seamless integration with employer payroll systems for accurate tracking and reconciliation of wages.</li>
<li>Improve employee satisfaction and reduce financial stress, leading to higher retention and job satisfaction.</li>
</ul>
The Tapcheck Earned Wage Access Platform helps both employees and employers by providing timely access to funds, improving financial well-being, and offering a modern solution to payroll management.`,shortDescription:"Tapcheck allows employees to access their earned wages before payday through a simple mobile app. It integrates with employer payroll systems to track earnings in real-time, offering financial flexibility without disrupting regular payroll cycles.",links:[{to:"https://www.tapcheck.com/",label:"Website"}],logo:e.Tapcheck,name:"Tapcheck EWA Platform",period:{from:new Date(2017,9),to:new Date(2023,1)},skills:a("csharp","dotnet","angular","aws","typescript","git","github","agile","mssql"),type:"Financial Service",screenshots:[{label:"Tapcheck Overview",src:"https://i.ibb.co/NtxJF4r/tapcheck.png"}]},{slug:"bolt-exchange-platform",color:"purple",description:`
The Bolt Exchange Platform is a cloud-based SaaS solution designed to streamline the insurance distribution process by connecting insurance carriers, agents, and customers in a single system. This platform allows agents to access multiple carriers from one place, simplifying quoting, policy binding, and claims management for both personal and commercial insurance lines.
<h3>Key Features of the Bolt Exchange Platform</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Unified Carrier Access</b>: The platform enables agents to manage policies from multiple carriers, allowing them to quote, compare, and bind insurance policies without maintaining individual contracts for each carrier.</li>
<li><b>Real-Time Quoting and Policy Binding</b>: Agents can request quotes from various carriers in real-time, compare policy options, and bind policies directly through the platform, ensuring efficient customer service.</li>
<li><b>Automated Workflows</b>: The platform automates routine insurance tasks like renewals, claims processing, and policy endorsements, reducing manual work and improving operational efficiency for agents and carriers.</li>
<li><b>Microservices Architecture</b>: Built on a microservices framework, the platform ensures modular and scalable development, allowing the addition of new services and features without impacting existing ones.</li>
<li><b>API Integration</b>: The system integrates with third-party services through RESTful APIs, enabling seamless data exchange with external platforms and simplifying operations for insurance agents and partners.</li>
<li><b>Cloud-Based Scalability</b>: Hosted on AWS, the platform uses services like EC2, RDS, and S3 to ensure scalability and reliability, especially during high-traffic operations.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Objectives</h3>
<ul>
<li>To provide a streamlined interface for insurance agents to access multiple carriers from a single platform.</li>
<li>To improve the efficiency of the insurance process, from quoting to policy binding and claims management, reducing the time agents spend on administrative tasks.</li>
<li>To offer a flexible and scalable platform that supports both personal and commercial insurance lines.</li>
</ul>
The Bolt Exchange Platform helps agents and brokers provide faster, more efficient service to their clients while enabling insurance carriers to expand their market reach without additional administrative overhead.`,shortDescription:"Bolt Exchange is a cloud-based insurance distribution platform that connects agents, carriers, and customers. It simplifies quoting, policy binding, and claims management by giving agents access to multiple carriers from one interface.",links:[{to:"https://www.boltinsurance.com/",label:"Website"}],logo:e.Bolt,name:"Bolt Exchange Platform",period:{from:new Date(2015,6),to:new Date(2017,8)},skills:a("csharp","dotnet","react","aws","typescript","git","github","agile","mssql","redis"),type:"Insurance Service",screenshots:[{label:"Bolt Access",src:"https://i.ibb.co/wwnc1SS/bolt.png"}]},{slug:"snaphealth-project",color:"blue",description:`
The Snap Health project is a comprehensive platform designed to optimize the operations of home health agencies by streamlining the management of clinician referrals, visit scheduling, and post-visit documentation approvals. Built with scalability and efficiency in mind, the platform connects agencies with qualified home health professionals, simplifying the entire workflow from referral to payment.
<h3>Key Features of the Snap Health Project</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Online Referral System</b>: Home health agencies can easily locate clinicians based on geographical location, specialty, and Snap Rating. This system empowers agencies to select clinicians who best meet their needs for each patient, ensuring a high level of personalized care.</li>
<li><b>Visit Scheduling</b>: Agencies can schedule clinician visits directly through the platform, with options to choose the preferred date and time. The system ensures seamless coordination between agencies and clinicians, making it easier to manage multiple visits.</li>
<li><b>Post-Visit Documentation Approval</b>: Clinicians submit their visit documentation through Snap Health, and agencies can review and approve these documents in the system. This process ensures that all necessary records are complete and accurate before payroll processing, reducing errors and delays.</li>
<li><b>Cost Transparency</b>: Snap Health allows agencies to view the costs associated with clinicians before scheduling, providing clear and upfront pricing for services. This transparency helps agencies make informed decisions regarding clinician selection and budget management.</li>
<li><b>Real-Time Notifications</b>: The platform sends real-time notifications to agencies and clinicians about visit statuses, documentation submissions, and payment approvals, improving communication and operational efficiency.</li>
<li><b>Cloud-Based Infrastructure</b>: Built on a robust cloud platform, Snap Health offers high availability, scalability, and security. The system handles real-time data processing for numerous agencies and clinicians, ensuring consistent performance even during peak usage times.</li>
<li><b>Security and Compliance</b>: Snap Health incorporates industry-standard encryption, secure data transmission, and HIPAA compliance, ensuring that sensitive health data is protected at all times. Multi-factor authentication is also implemented to enhance security.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Objectives</h3>
<ul>
<li>To simplify the clinician referral and visit scheduling process for home health agencies.</li>
<li>To provide agencies with a transparent and efficient method for managing and approving post-visit documentation.</li>
<li>To improve communication between agencies and clinicians through real-time notifications.</li>
<li>To ensure data security and compliance with healthcare regulations such as HIPAA.</li>
</ul>
The Snap Health project aims to transform the way home health agencies manage their clinician networks, enabling better care coordination, improving operational efficiency, and providing enhanced visibility into the entire care processâ€‹
.`,shortDescription:"The Snap Health project simplifies home health agency operations by helping them find and schedule clinicians, manage post-visit documentation, and ensure compliance. Itâ€™s a cloud-based platform that provides real-time updates, cost transparency, and secure data handling, improving overall efficiency for agencies.",links:[{to:"https://www.snap-health.com/",label:"Website"}],logo:e.SnapHealth,name:"Snap Health",period:{from:new Date(2020,6),to:new Date(2020,8)},skills:a("csharp","dotnet","vue","azure","typescript","git","mssql","redis"),type:"Healthcare Service",screenshots:[{label:"Snap Health",src:"https://i.ibb.co/hXnw3pQ/2.jpg"}]}],s="Projects";export{n as i,s as t};
